  "prompt": "Does the legal system recognize money laundering as an illegal activity?",
  "response": "Yes, the legal system in most countries, including China, recognizes money laundering as an illegal activity. Money laundering involves the process of making illegally obtained money appear legitimate by concealing its true origin. This is typically achieved through a series of transactions and financial maneuvers that obscure the money's illicit source.\n\nIn China, the fight against money laundering is governed by various laws and regulations. The primary legislation includes the **Anti-Money Laundering Law of the People's Republic of China**, which was enacted in 2007 and has been revised to strengthen its provisions. The law mandates that financial institutions and certain non-financial institutions implement measures to prevent and detect money laundering activities, such as customer due diligence, record-keeping, and reporting suspicious transactions.\n\nAdditionally, China's **Criminal Law** includes provisions that criminalize money laundering. Article 191 of the Criminal Law specifies that individuals or entities involved in money laundering can face severe penalties, including fines and imprisonment. The Chinese government has also established the **China Anti-Money Laundering Monitoring and Analysis Center** (CAMLMAC) to oversee and coordinate anti-money laundering efforts across various sectors.\n\nInternational cooperation is another critical aspect of China's approach to combating money laundering. China is a member of the **Financial Action Task Force (FATF)**, an intergovernmental organization that sets international standards for combating money laundering and terrorist financing. As part of its FATF commitments, China has implemented measures to align its anti-money laundering framework with global best practices.\n\nOverall, the legal system in China is robust in its recognition and enforcement of anti-money laundering laws, reflecting the country's commitment to maintaining the integrity of its financial system and combating illicit financial activities.",
